item.title: 97 Bodies Recovered From Pakistan International Airlines Crash
item.description: The plane crashed Friday as it reached Karachi, slamming into a residential area on the edge of the airport. Two passengers survived and weren’t badly hurt, an escape described as “miraculous” by the authorities.

item.title: Jobless Migrants Returning Home From Oil-Rich Countries
item.description: Legions of foreign workers are leaving Gulf nations amid the coronavirus pandemic, part of a global shift of migrant labor that is depriving their native lands of much-needed remittances.

item.title: As Coronavirus Spreads in Nicaragua, Official Denials Amplify Risk
item.description: Nicaragua has become a coronavirus hot spot but its authoritarian leader is endangering public health by ignoring the threat and hiding infection data, according to doctors and relatives of victims.

item.title: During Coronavirus, Jews Around the World Stand In to Say the Kaddish
item.description: The Covid-19 pandemic has upended mourning around the world, with many Jewish rituals falling to whomever can perform them.

item.title: Coronavirus Might Become 'Fixture' in Africa for Years
item.description: From Tanzania to Cameroon and from Somalia to Nigeria, health workers are reporting a reality that bears little resemblance to the official data, with hot spots emerging in countries with few resources to tackle them.

item.title: China's Move to Dismantle Hong Kong's Autonomy Poses Dilemma for U.S. Policy
item.description: China’s plan to tighten control over Hong Kong presents the U.S. with tough choices between tolerating Beijing’s incursion on the territory’s semiautonomy and retaliating without hurting its largely pro-Western population.
